    THEME written and designed by:
        Tuxedo Joe <http://github.com/tuxedojoe> for Tux4Ubuntu Initiative <http://tux4ubuntu.blogspot.com>. 
        Based on the rEFInd OS X theme created by: naymlexwun <http://naymlezwun.deviantart.com/art/rEFInd-OS-X-Theme-469807750>
        License: Creative Commons Attribution - Noncommercial 3.0 License <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/>

    TUX ILLUSTRATION by:
        Larry Ewing, at: <http://isc.tamu.edu/~lewing/linux/>
        Redrawn in Inkscape by: Garrett LeSage: <https://github.com/garrett/Tux>
        License: Public domain <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>

    FONT AND GREY BACKGROUND COLOR CODE created by:
        naymlexwun <http://naymlezwun.deviantart.com/art/rEFInd-OS-X-Theme-469807750>
        License: Creative Commons Attribution - Noncommercial 3.0 License <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/3.0/>

    BASE HDD ICON created and designed by:
        Tuxedo Joe <http://github.com/tuxedojoe> for Tux4Ubuntu Initiative <http://tux4ubuntu.blogspot.com>. 
        Inspired by the Sleek Aluminium Hard Drive tutorial at: Design Instruct <http://designinstruct.com/graphic-design/how-to-make-a-sleek-aluminium-hard-drive-in-photoshop/>
        LED light design was created and modified from the original files created by NTDesign shown in this video: <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EvmVUZx-nZo>

    ARROWS, FUNCTIONALITIES AND TOOLS ICONS created and designed by:
        Tuxedo Joe <http://github.com/tuxedojoe> for Tux4Ubuntu Initiative <http://tux4ubuntu.blogspot.com>. 
        Inspired by icons used by rEFInd project, which in turn took them from AwOken 2.5:
        - The AwOken 2.5 icon set
        - Source: http://alecive.deviantart.com/art/AwOken-163570862
        - Copyright (c) 2013 by Alessandro Roncone (aka alecive on DeviantArt)
        - License: Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 (CC-SA 3.0)

        Except for the func_csr_rotate.png were the outlines were taken from this free to use icon: http://www.freeiconspng.com/free-images/shield-png-23097 

        An apple and a flag is used to represent Apple's rescue tools and Microsoft Windows' rescue tool. If by any chance,
        Apple, or Microsoft should argue this is copyright infringement (We're looking at you Apple) we will happily remove these icons.

    PNG ICONS ON TOP OF HDD BASE, if not specified below, are created by:
        Gustavo Castro <https://github.com/gustawho>
        Found here: https://github.com/gustawho/grub2-theme-breeze/tree/master/breeze/icons
        License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 License <https://github.com/gustawho/grub2-theme-breeze/blob/master/LICENSE>

        - CLOVER, NETWORK, LEGACY, HWTEST, GUMMIBOOT AND CRUNCHBAG OS ICONS PNGS were recieved from the standard rEFInd theme created by:
        Roderick W. Smith <https://sourceforge.net/u/srs5694/profile/> and others contributing to the rEFInd project.
        Found here:  https://sourceforge.net/projects/refind/      
        License: Specified in the README file inside the "icons"-folder in the rEFInd project version 0.10.4 <https://sourceforge.net/projects/refind/files/latest/download?source=files>

        - MACOS is a trademark of Apple Inc. To ensure not using the original logo Apple is using for their OS, the icon were instead created by typing macOS with Arial, and squeezing the "OS" part a bit.
        
        - MANDRIVA icon was found here <https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/34/Mandriva-Logo.svg>
        
        - HAIKU icon was found here <http://cgit.haiku-os.org/haiku/plain/data/artwork/HAIKU%20logo%20-%20black.svg>

        - FRUGALWARE icon was found here: <http://frugalware.org/>

        - GOOGLE CHROME icon was created by <Icomoon> found here: <http://www.flaticon.com/free-icon/chrome_23689>

        - DRAGON FLY icon from: <https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2a/DragonFly_BSD_Logo_svg.svg/1280px-DragonFly_BSD_Logo_svg.svg.png>

        - OPENBSD icon from <https://www.shareicon.net/openbsd-102884>

        All these icons has been modified in size and color overlay to conform to a united design.